<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id27fad1af-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419" identifier="/us/usc/t45/s1313"><num value="1313">§ 1313.</num><heading> Fees</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id27fad1b0-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419" identifier="/us/usc/t45/s1313/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Investment banking firm fees</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Transportation, in consultation with the Secretary of the Treasury, shall agree to pay to investment banking firms and other persons participating with such firms in the public offering the absolute minimum amount in fees necessary to carry out the public offering.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id27fad1b1-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419" identifier="/us/usc/t45/s1313/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Costs of public offering</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">All costs of the public offering payable by the Secretary of Transportation shall be paid from the proceeds of the public offering.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id27fad1b2-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/509/tIV/s4013">Pub. L. 99–509, title IV, § 4013</ref>, <date date="1986-10-21">Oct. 21, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/1897">100 Stat. 1897</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
